I was feeling quite heartbroken and heavy the week I chatted with Russell, but he was absolutely kind, inquisitive and insightful as can be. I am very grateful for the opportunity to chat and to share parts of my story. Hope we can get the dogs together next. 

Link in bio to view a segment on YouTube! Or catch the whole 1 hour 38 minute conversation via @russellbrand’s podcast Under a the Skin on @hearluminary.

node.text:
Join @oreggieglobal, me, Benji, and the energy of people across the globe as we connect on the power of TRANSITION. Take some some for the breath, and lovingly ask yourself... what wisdom of the winter will you take with you into Spring? Remember... how you move matters. 

Thank you so much to Reggie for sharing his heart and teachings so freely. Becoming friends with you is definitely a gift I am grateful and honored to take with me into Spring. 
ALSO, FELIZ CUMPLEAÑOS @activepeaceyoga! Join Reggie for practice this weekend! See his latest post for the schedule Saturday and Sunday. 
Monday, your new Yoga For Renewal practice hits YWA YouTube channel - expect a lot of good hip work. 

We got you covered baby. 
CUE: What’s Going On 🎶 

Happy FWFG FRIDAY 🐣💜
#activepeaceyoga #findwhatfeelsgood

As a cattle dog, Benji is just the best at communicating and herding! He really loves to take naps... but he also really loves to help! He quite enjoys a good task to focus on when it’s time to get to work. He likes to bring people together (he is dictating this to me now) he likes to see people be good to each other, and he loves toys and playing - especially tennis. Favorite food: chips. Favorite person: you. (oh he is talking to me!)

💙💜🧡💖💛💚🤎
I could not be more proud of him and am excited to share VOTE WITH BENJI, with all of you! 

With art and animation by the amazing  @wilbo_rose , original music by the one and only @spacejason3d , and story by @the_realjeffmills and myself, inspiration by Benji and our beloved community. Sending a special thank you and high five to @the_realjeffmills for producing and directing this baby. While we missed going on tour this year, we are certainly grateful to know we can always create, engage, and share in both fun and meaningful conversation with all of you. For me, it has always been a huge part of what taking our yoga off the mat looks like. (Though we do miss those 3 hour hug lines!) 

Please join us, join Benji, and let’s get out the vote. 🗳

Benji has launched a friendly and easy to use website that can assist you with all your voting needs like checking registration, finding your poll location, or reading up on Covid 19 voting info.

Visit www.votewithbenji.com and share with your friends!
#votewithbenji #votéconbenji #vote

⁣
⁣
I’m super excited to be taking over Adriene’s instagram today to connect with you all in such a transformative way.⁣
⁣
I’m Tie Simpson, a mother of two, Yoga Instructor, Artist, Wellness Influencer, Content Creator, and the Founder of @sistersofyoga who’s hosting the #ShareTheMicNow Yoga Edition this weekend. I’ve been practicing yoga and on my spiritual journey for about 7 years now, and I’m so incredibly grateful to spend the day with you. ⁣
⁣
Stay tuned today in the FEED + STORIES, where I’ll be sharing my yoga philosophy, my practice, “A Day In The Life” with me, resources on how you can help to expand the collective forward, and connecting through Q&A.
⁣
THANK YOU ADRIENE for your love, light, and your unwavering support of this initiative to amplifying black and brown voices in the yoga and wellness community.⁣
⁣
I’ll be going LIVE today at 12:20PM EST to connect with you all! ⁣
12:30PM- @phyllicia.bonanno will lead us in a collective healing soundbath meditation⁣
1PM EST- @iamrachelricketts will share her wisdom and heart work centered around dismantling racism through spiritual activism. ⁣
⁣
Let’s connect below. 🥰👇🏾 Say Hiiii, and tell me one thing you’re grateful for today!

This precious angel exhibits such patience as I drill and dabble away each day at my desk. I love him. I love spending time with him. And uniquely, through our yoga practices, so do a lot of you - I think. 
There is a lot of scary s*** going on in the world and in our respective communities. If you’re reading this, I invite you in. Benji may have a little something in the works for us. Or so I hear. Stay tuned. 

September often brings palatable gifts to us. Even (especially) when things feel dark. For those who wish to connect, reset, and stay present with it all - come practice. It’s free. Sign up for my love letter to receive your September calendar and yoga playlist this Sunday. 
Then you will be ready… 
To begin
Again. 

All my love.

I believe that if we embody the principles of Yoga in the practice, we can embody them off the mat too. If everyone was more comfortable, confident in their own skin, able to love and understand themselves better, we may be able to offer that same confidence, love, and understanding to others with more authentic energy and ease. 🤍🖤 link in bio to new blog with @adidas - geared toward beginners but resonant for all right now, perhaps. 

Yoga is the ultimate path that guides conscious living, and equips us with a healthy body and mental state. You will learn to breathe better, to live better, and to use the tools of pranayama to manage your life with less anxiety, improved sleep, and a centered state of sustainable energy. 

#yogaforall see you on the mat!
